stylometry:
SUMPRODUCT: This allows two sets of data to be multiplied together and then added. For example if you have Columns A and B, rows 2-8 in each one and you want to know what the sum would be if you did A2*B2+A3*B3+...+A8*B8, instead you can do SUMPRODUCT and highlight to data set and it will do it for you. 

VLOOKUP: This allows you to look up a specific data cell from a specific set. The best example is when we were figuring out shortest path and wanted to know the names of the specific cities and we used VLOOKUP to take the number of the destination and literally look up the corisponding city, this saves the business time and is incredibly easy to do. 

SUMIF: This does exactly what it says, if this happens then add this.

IF: This states if this then do this, if not then do this. Many times it is if a cell is > 0, then this number goes in, if not then this goes in. (=IF(A4>0,B2, B4)) This states if the value in A4 is greater than zero the cell should contain the value that is in B2, if A4 is not greater than 0 then the value in B4 is used instead.
